<article>
    <h1>Sig&#xAD;na&#xAD;ture And New Moon&#xAD;cakes At Yan</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Can­tonese res­tau­rant Yan has re­leased five sig­na­ture tra­di­tional moon­cakes and a snowskin cre­ation. They come in sets of four in two-tiered boxes. The Mix & Match Set ($68 nett) com­prises flavours like White Lo­tus Paste Moon­cakes, Thou­sand Layer Yam Moon­cakes and Mao Shan Wang Durian Snowskin Moon­cakes. Guests can cre­ate their own box by pick­ing four pieces from the White Lo­tus Paste Moon­cakes and the Thou­sand Layer Yam Moon­cakes ranges. Avail­able for pickup, drive-through pickup and de­liv­ery ($14 nett, free for or­ders of 50 boxes and above). Till Mon­day, cus­tomers will get 25 per cent off di­rect on­line pur­chases. From Tues­day to Aug 31, early-bird or­ders are en­ti­tled to a 20 per cent dis­count.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Yan, 05-02 Na­tional Gallery Sin­ga­pore, 1 St An­drew’s Road</p>
    <p>MRT: City Hall WHEN: Till Oct 1; de­liv­ery & col­lec­tion from Aug 31</p>
    <p>TEL: Call 6384-5585 or What­sApp 9769-4283 INFO: www.yan.com.sg/es­tore/moon­cakes</p>


